10.10am Hello everyone, welcome to the second day from the SCG. Lovely morning, looks like a batting day...but England are at the crease. Yesterday felt like a bit of celebration for Australia, freewheeling batting, almost a shot-a-ball in the afternoon, and 326 from 5 for 97 was an excellent recovery. As ever, it seems, it was Brad Haddin who turned the day even though Steven Smith ended with the hundred. For England, Ben Stokes claimed a six-wicket haul but unless the visitors bat better than they have all series it won't mean much. George Dobell argues that it's the national set-up that is causing the problems.
